data.using-the-generated-client#Using the gen:
import { Client as TokenClient } from './.soroban/stellar__token'
const client = new TokenClient({
  contractId: '',
  networkPassphrase: 'Public Global Stellar Network ; September 2015',
  rpcUrl: 'https://mainnet.stellar.validationcloud.io/v1/xycSmFnKMsLaOUPNGa6qFHNreHmf',
})
// Call a function — fully typed
const balance = await client.balance({ id: 'GABC123...' })

data.json-output#JSON output:
Use --json to get machine-readable output suitable for piping:
soropkg inspect CAQQR5S... --json | jq '.functions[0]'
{
  "name": "deposit",
  "inputs": [
    { "name": "from",   "type": "Address" },
    { "name": "pool",   "type": "Address" },
    { "name": "amount", "type": "i128" }
  ],
  "output": "i128"
}
The interface is read directly from the live deployed WASM on the specified network. If a contract has been upgraded since it was published to the registry, inspect will always show the current live interface.
